1) 'Photograph of Miss Julia Neilson and Mr Fred Terry,12" x 10" size, No 45634-1. 3) 'Photograph of Miss Julia Neilson and Mr Fred Terry,12" x 10" size, No 45634-4. Group on stage, Mr Robertshaw standing on steps at right of picture, man with beard standing near foot of steps resting left hand on side of seat, Miss Neilson standing in the centre gesticulating with right hand. Mr Terry standing near her with hands on hips, jester standing at left'. 4cm x 4cm.

7) 'Photograph of Miss Julia Neilson and Mr Jerold Robertshaw, No 45636-7. Miss Neilson standing forward side faced, with sword in right hand and left hand stretched out. Mr Robertshaw with sword in right hand and left arm stretched out, fencing across table'. 4cm x 4cm.

8) 'Photograph of Miss Julia Neilson and Mr Jerold Robertshaw, 12" x 10" size No 45636-5. Mr Robertshaw standing with left arm stretched out, holding sword over left shoulder in right hand. Miss Neilson back view, holding sword downwards in right hand'. 4cm x 4cm.

9) 'Photograph of 'Dorothy o' the Hall', 12" x 10" size, No 45636-3. Group of four, man standing in centre, Fred Terry kneeling on left knee. Miss Julia standing full length, side face, with left hand in front, jester standing behind a wall with right hand raised'. 4cm x 4cm.

10) 'Photograph of 'Dorothy o' the Hall' 12" x 10" size, No 45636-4. Group on stage, Mr Robertshaw standing at right with hand on belt, Mr Terry standing back view, holding sword in right hand facing crowd in doorway at back. Miss Neilson standing holding jester by the arm, wearing long veil thrown over her head and falling to ground'. 4cm x 4cm.

11) 'Photograph of 'Dorothy o' the Hall' 12" x 10" size, No 45636-12. Miss Neilson standing holding jester by the arm, wearing long veil thrown over her head and falling to ground'. 4cm x 5cm.

12) 'Photograph of Julia Neilson and Jerold Robertshaw, 12" x 10" size, No 45636-9. Mr Robertshaw standing full length with sword in right hand. Miss Julia Neilson sitting on the ground with both hands against table'. 4cm x 5cm.

13) 'Photograph of J C Edwards, whole plate size, No 45626, sitting down, almost full face, with right arm resting upon seat, left hand holding top of sword, wearing Elizabethan costume'. 3cm x 4cm.

14) 'Photograph of Miss Julia Neilson and Jerold Robertshaw, No 45636-8. Miss Neilson stooping down with hands in front of her, looking at Mr Robertshaw, who is holding sword in right hand'. 4cm x 5cm.

15) 'Photograph of Mr Fred Terry, whole plate size, No 45623-2, standing with right arm resting on seat, left hand on hip'. 3cm x 3cm.
